}} || 1\u20130 || 3\u20130 || Friendly\n|-\n| 20. || 29 June 1994 || [[Citrus Bowl]], [[Orlando]], United States || align=left| {{fb|MAR}} || 1\u20130 || 2\u20131 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup]]\n|-\n| 21. || 4 July 1994 || Citrus Bowl, Orlando, United States || align=left| {{fb|IRL}} || 1\u20130 || 2\u20130 || 1994 FIFA World Cup\n|-\n| 22. || 9 July 1994 || [[Cotton Bowl (stadium)|Cotton Bowl]], [[Dallas]], United States || align=left| {{fb|BRA}} || 1\u20132 || 2\u20133 || 1994 FIFA World Cup\n|-\n| 23. || 29 March 1995 || De Kuip, Rotterdam, Netherlands || align=left| {{flagicon|MLT}} Malta || 2\u20130 || 4\u20130 || [[UEFA Euro 1996 qualifying Group 5|UEFA Euro 1996 qualifying]]\n|-\n| 24. || 4 June 1996 || De Kuip, Rotterdam, Netherlands || align=left| {{flagicon|IRL}} Republic of Ireland || 1\u20131 || 3\u20131 || Friendly\n|-\n| 25. || 13 June 1996 || [[Villa Park]], Birmingham, England || align=left| {{fb|SWI}} || 2\u20130 || 2\u20130 || [[UEFA Euro 1996]]\n|-\n| 26. || 9 November 1996 || Philips Stadion, Eindhoven, Netherlands || align=left| {{fb|WAL}} || 1\u20130 || 7\u20131 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|1998 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 27. || 9 November 1996 || Philips Stadion, Eindhoven, Netherlands || align=left| {{flagicon|WAL}} Wales || 6\u20130 || 7\u20131 || 1998 FIFA World Cup qualification\n|-\n| 28. || 9 November 1996 || Philips Stadion, Eindhoven, Netherlands || align=left| {{flagicon|WAL}} Wales || 7\u20131 || 7\u20131 || 1998 FIFA World Cup qualification\n|-\n| 29. || 12 December 1996 || [[King Baudouin Stadium]], Brussels, Belgium || align=left| {{fb|BEL}} || 1\u20130 || 3\u20130 || 1998 FIFA World Cup qualification\n|-\n| 30. || 26 February 1997 || [[Parc des Princes]], Paris, France || align=left| {{fb|FRA}} || 1\u20130 || 1\u20132 || Friendly\n|-\n| 31. || 30 April 1997 || [[Stadio Olimpico (San Marino)|Stadio Olimpico]], [[Serravalle (San Marino)|Serravalle]], San Marino || align=left| {{fb|SMR}} || 1\u20130 || 6\u20130 || 1998 FIFA World Cup qualification\n|-\n| 32. || 30 April 1997 || Stadio Olimpico (San Marino), Serravalle, San Marino || align=left| {{flagicon|SMR}} San Marino || 6\u20130 || 6\u20130 || 1998 FIFA World Cup qualification\n|-\n| 33. || 6 September 1997 || [[Amsterdam ArenA]], Amsterdam, Netherlands || align=left| {{fb|BEL}} || 3\u20131 || 3\u20131 || 1998 FIFA World Cup qualification\n|-\n| 34. || 20 June 1998 || [[Stade V\u00e9lodrome]], [[Marseille]], France || align=left| {{fb|KOR}} || 3\u20130 || 5\u20130 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup]]\n|-\n| 35. || 29 June 1998 || [[Stade de Toulouse]], [[Toulouse]], France || align=left| {{fb|YUG}} || 1\u20130 || 2\u20131 || 1998 FIFA World Cup\n|-\n| 36. || 4 July 1998 || Stade V\u00e9lodrome, Marseille, France || align=left| {{fb|ARG}} || 2\u20131 || 2\u20131 || 1998 FIFA World Cup\n|-\n| 37. || 9 October 1999 || Amsterdam Arena, Amsterdam, Netherlands || align=left| {{flagicon|BRA}} Brazil || 1\u20130 || 2\u20132 || Friendly\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Ajax'''\n*[[Eredivisie]]: [[1989\u201390 Eredivisie|1989\u201390]]\n*[[KNVB Cup]]: [[1986\u201387 KNVB Cup|1986\u201387]], [[1992\u201393 KNVB Cup|1992\u201393]]\n*[[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|European Cup Winners' Cup]]: [[1986\u201387 European Cup Winners' Cup|1986\u201387]]\n*[[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]: [[1991\u201392 UEFA Cup|1991\u201392]]\n\n'''Inter Milan'''\n*UEFA Cup: [[1993\u201394 UEFA Cup|1993\u201394]]\n\n'''Arsenal'''\n*[[Premier League]]: [[1997\u201398 FA Premier League|1997\u201398]], [[2001\u201302 FA Premier League|2001\u201302]], [[2003\u201304 FA Premier League|2003\u201304]]<ref name=PremProfile>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/991/Dennis-Bergkamp/overview |title=Dennis Bergkamp: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=27 September 2018}}</ref>\n*[[FA Cup]]: [[1997\u201398 FA Cup|1997\u201398]], [[2001\u201302 FA Cup|2001\u201302]], [[2002\u201303 FA Cup|2002\u201303]], [[2004\u201305 FA Cup|2004\u201305]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/features/dennis-bergkamp|title=Dennis Bergkamp|website=www.arsenal.com|access-date=28 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[FA Community Shield|FA Charity/Community Shield]]: [[1998 FA Charity Shield|1998]], [[2002 FA Community Shield|2002]], [[2004 FA Community Shield|2004]]\n\n===Individual===\nBergkamp has received several accolades during his playing career. He twice finished in third place for the [[1993 FIFA World Player of the Year|1993]] and [[1997 FIFA World Player of the Year|1996]] [[FIFA World Player of the Year]] award and was named in [[FIFA 100]], a list compiled by footballer [[Pel\u00e9]] of the 125 greatest living footballers.<ref name=Fifa100>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2004/mar/04/newsstory.sport15 |title=The Fifa 100 |date=4 March 2004 |accessdate=15 December 2011 |work=The Guardian|location=London}}</ref> In his club career, Bergkamp won two successive [[Dutch Footballer of the Year]] awards in 1991 and 1992 and was the [[Eredivisie#Top scorers|Eredivisie Top Scorer]] winner for three consecutive seasons (1990\u201391 to 1992\u201393). He was named the [[FWA Footballer of the Year]] and [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]] in April and May 1998 and made the [[PFA Team of the Year]] for the 1997\u201398 season. Bergkamp also achieved a unique feat in being voted first, second and third on [[Match of the Day]]'s [[BBC Goal of the Month|Goal of the Month]] competition in August 1997.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Joy of Six: classiest hat-tricks |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2007/sep/11/newsstory.sport9 |work=[[guardian.co.uk]] |location=London |date=11 September 2007 |accessdate=18 December 2011 }}</ref> For his national team, Bergkamp was the top goalscorer at Euro 1992 and was selected in the [[FIFA World Cup awards#All-Star Team|FIFA World Cup All-Star Team]] for the 1998 World Cup.\n\nIn April 2007, Bergkamp was inducted into the [[English Football Hall of Fame]] by viewers of BBC's ''[[Football Focus]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arsenal.com/news/news-archive/dennis-bergkand-voted-into-hall-of-fame |title=Dennis Bergkamp voted into Hall of Fame |date=3 September 2007 |accessdate=15 December 2011 |publisher=Arsenal.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130603204724/http://www.arsenal.com/news/news-archive/dennis-bergkand-voted-into-hall-of-fame |archivedate=3 June 2013}}</ref> A year later, he was voted second by Arsenal fans behind Thierry Henry in a list of the ''50 Gunners Greatest Players''.<ref name=\"Gunners' Greatest\"/> In February 2014, Arsenal unveiled a statue of Bergkamp outside the Emirates Stadium to honour his time at the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal unveil Dennis Bergkamp statue|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-london-26303200|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=9 October 2014|date=22 February 2014}}</ref> A statue of Dennis Bergkamp will be erected outside the KNVB headquarters in [[Zeist]], as he has been chosen as the best Dutch international player from 1990 to 2015. The statue will join those of ''the eleven of the century'', erected in 1999, alongside statues of Johan Cruyff, [[Ruud Gullit]], [[Frank Rijkaard]] and Marco van Basten, amongst others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trouw.nl/tr/nl/4508/Sport/article/detail/3811022/2014/12/13/Bergkamp-krijgt-standbeeld-bij-KNVB.dhtml|title=Bergkamp krijgt standbeeld bij KNVB|work=TROUW}}</ref>\n\nA summary of Bergkamp's individual achievements are as follows in chronological order:\n\n[[File:Dennis Bergkamp statue 2.jpg|thumbnail|Bergkamp statue outside the [[Emirates Stadium]]]]\n\n*[[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands All-Time Top Scorer]]: [[Netherlands national football team records#Most goals scored|1998\u20132003]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bergkamp-intlg.html|title=Dennis Bergkamp \u2013 Goals in international matches|website=RSSSF.com}}</ref>\n*[[Dutch Footballer of the Year#Dutch Football Talent of the Year|Dutch Football Talent of the Year]]: 1990<ref name=\"RSSSF\">{{cite web|url= http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/nedpoy.html|title=Netherlands \u2013 Player of the Year and Other Awards|work=RSSSF|accessdate=22 March 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Eredivisie#Top scorers|Eredivisie Top Scorer]]: 1990\u201391, 1991\u201392, 1992\u201393<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eredivisiestats.nl/topscorers.php|title=Top Scorers|website=Eredivisie Stats.nl}}</ref>\n*[[Dutch Footballer of the Year#Dutch Footballers of the Year|Dutch Footballer of the Year]]: 1991,<ref name=\"RSSSF\"/> 1992<ref name=\"RSSSF\"/>\n*[[UEFA Euro 1992#Goal scorers|UEFA European Football Championship Top Scorer]]: 1992<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=1887223.html|title=Torres receives adidas Golden Boot|accessdate=22 March 2015|publisher=UEFA.com}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA European Championship Teams of the Tournament#Sweden 1992|UEFA European Football Championship Teams of the Tournament]]: 1992<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=1625178.html|title=UEFA 1992 Team of the Tournament|date=|work=UEFA.com|accessdate=22 March 2015}}</ref>\n*[[IFFHS#IFFHS' World's Top Goal Scorer of the Year|IFFHS World's Top Goal Scorer of the Year]]: 1992<ref>{{cite web|url=http://iffhs.com/gala/13|title=THE WORLD\u2019S BEST TOP GOAL SCORER|accessdate=21 March 2020|publisher=IFFHS.com}}</ref>\n*[[Ballon d'Or (1956\u20132009)|Ballon d'Or]] \u2013 Runner-up: 1993;<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/europa-poy93.html|title=European Footballer of the Year (\"Ballon d'Or\") 1993|work=RSSSF|accessdate=14 April 2015 }}</ref> Third place: 1992<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/europa-poy92.html|title=European Footballer of the Year (\"Ballon d'Or\") 1992|work=RSSSF|accessdate=14 April 2015 }}</ref>\n*[[FIFA World Player of the Year]] \u2013 Bronze Award: 1993,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/ballon-dor/history/edition=1993/overview.html|title=Baggio takes 1993 World Player honour|accessdate=22 March 2015|publisher=FIFA.com}}</ref> 1997<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zimbio.com/photos/Dennis+Bergkamp/FILE+Profile+Dennis+Bergkamp/UxeP0JmNaxd|title=Dennis Bergkamp with the FIFA Player of the Year Bronze award|accessdate=22 March 2015}}</ref>\n*[[List of UEFA Cup and Europa League top scorers#Winners by seasons|UEFA Cup Top Scorer]]: 1993\u201394<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/goalgetter/uefa-cup-1993-1994/|title=Europa League 1993/1994 \" Top Scorer|publisher=WorldFootball.net|accessdate=26 June 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Premier League Player of the Month]]: [[1997\u201398 FA Premier League#Monthly awards|August 1997]], September 1997, [[2001\u201302 FA Premier League#Monthly awards|March 2002]], [[2003\u201304 FA Premier League#Monthly awards|February 2004]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n*[[PFA Team of the Year]]: [[PFA Team of the Year (1990s)#FA Premier League 6|1997\u201398 Premier League]]\n*[[FWA Footballer of the Year]]: 1997\u201398\n*[[PFA Players' Player of the Year]]: 1997\u201398\n*[[BBC Goal of the Season|Premier League Goal of the Season]]: 1997\u201398, 2001\u201302<ref name=\"MOTD\">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/sports_talk/1060082.stm|title=Ask Albert - Number 8|date=7 December 2011|accessdate=16 December 2011 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n*[[Premier League]] top assist provider: [[1998\u201399 Premier League|1998\u201399]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/history/1998-99|title=1998/99 Season Review|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#All-Star Team|FIFA World Cup All-Star Team]]: [[FIFA World Cup 1998#All-star team|1998]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/newscentre/news/newsid=71747/index.html|title=FIFA Technical Study Group designates MasterCard All-Star Team|date=10 July 1998|accessdate=22 March 2015|publisher=FIFA.com}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA World Cup]] top assist provider: [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.planetworldcup.com/CUPS/1998/wc98statistics.html |title=Planet World Cup - 1998 - Statistics |publisher=Planet World Cup |access-date=12 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA 100]]<ref name=Fifa100/>\n*[[English Football Hall of Fame]]: 2007<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalfootballmuseum.com/halloffame/dennis-bergkamp|title=DENNIS BERGKAMP|website=National Football Museum.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n'''Works cited'''\n* {{cite book |last=Gouw |first=P. |title=Griekse atleten in de Romeinse Keizertijd: 31 v. Chr. \u2013 400 n. Chr. |year=2009 |publisher=Amsterdam University Press |location=Amsterdam |isbn=90-5629-576-4 |ref = {{sfnRef|Gouw}} }}\n* {{cite book |last=Kuper |first=Simon |title=The Football Men: Up Close with the Giants of the Modern Game |year=2011 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |location=London |isbn=978-0-85720-160-7 |ref = {{sfnRef|Kuper}} }}\n* {{cite book |last=Palmer |first=Myles |title=The Professor: Ars\u00e8ne Wenger |year=2008 |publisher=Virgin Books |location=London |isbn=0-7535-1097-9 |ref = {{sfnRef|Palmer}} }}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Sister project links|wikt=no|b=no|v=no|q=no}}\n* {{FIFA player}}\n* [http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=633 Statistics] at Soccerbase.com\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140228215404/http://www.arsenal.com/history/profiles/48/dennis-bergkamp Dennis Bergkamp profile] at Arsenal.com\n* {{wvo|1073}}\n* [http://www.iffhs.de/index.php/posts/408 Dennis Bergkamp presentation] at IFHHS.de\n\n{{Navboxes\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| title = Awards\n| list1 = \n{{UEFA Euro 1992 Team of the Tournament}}\n{{1998 FIFA World Cup Team of the Tournament}}\n{{Eredivisie top scorers}}\n{{UEFA European Championship top scorers}}\n{{UEFA Europa League top scorers}}\n{{PFA Players' Player of the Year}}\n{{FWA Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Dutch Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Dutch Football Talent of the Year}}\n{{AFC Ajax Player of the Year}}\n{{Arsenal F.C. Player of the Year}}