y final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 7, 2019|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| endrating7       =\n| season7          = 2019\u201320\n| rank7            = \n| viewers7         = \n\n}}\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Nominee\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"12\"| 2014\n| [[Golden Globe Award]]s<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000292/2014?ref_=ttawd_ev_1|title=Golden Globes, USA (2014)|website=[[Internet Movie Database]]|accessdate=January 11, 2014}}</ref>\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Television Series Drama|Best Actor \u2013 Television Series Drama]]\n| James Spader\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[People's Choice Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000530/2014?ref_=ttawd_ev_2|title=People's Choice Awards (2014)|website=Internet Movie Database|accessdate=January 11, 2014}}</ref>\n| [[People's Choice Awards|Favorite New Television Drama]]\n| ''The Blacklist''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| [[Entertainment Weekly]]<br />Season Finale Awards<ref>{{cite journal|last=Bierly|first=Mandi|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/gallery/0,,20593459_20820828,00.html|title=TV Season Finale Awards: YOUR 2014 Winners|date=May 28, 2014|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=August 18, 2014}}</ref>\n| Best Non-Romantic Cliffhanger\n| rowspan=\"6\"| \"Berlin (No. 8) Conclusion\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Funniest Moment in a Drama\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Weakest/Most Divisive Twist\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Final Shot\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Most Likely to Earn Someone an Emmy Nomination\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Biggest Regret That I Didn't See It, I Just Heard or Read About It\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[66th Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards|Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards]]\n| Outstanding Stunt Coordination for a Drama Series, Miniseries, or Movie\n| ''The Blacklist''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers Awards|ASCAP Film and Television Music Awar