ey, Chad Hessler, Cort Hessler, Donald John Hewitt, Scott Kelly, Pete Klein, Drew Leary, Luke Lesko, Roberto Lopez, Terence Lorino, Stephen Mann, Michael Matera, Chazz Menendez, Luis Moco, Declan Mulvey, James Newman, Josiah Nolan, Christopher Parker, Ashley Pynn, Jodi Michelle Pynn, Bob Roseman, Akos Schenek, Hannah Scott, Derrick Simmons, Brian Smyj, Matt Triplett, Thad Turner, and Aaron Vexler.\n{{refend}}\n\n==Other media==\n\n===Comics===\n[[Titan Books]] released an official comic book series based on the series, written by Nicole Phillips and drawn by Beni Lobel. The series' crew is working in the project as well.\n\nEditor David Leach told ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' that the comic is \"a true extension of the television series\" giving \"new dimensions of the characters that have captured the audiences worldwide\". The series will open with a six-issue story arc, which will be \"a journey deep into the dark world of international espionage, conspiracies and intrigue on a global scale\".\n\nIssue #1 was launched July 22, 2015, in both comic book and digital stores.<ref>{{cite journal |last=McMillan |first=Graeme |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/nbcs-blacklist-coming-comics-summer-788693 |title=NBC's 'The Blacklist' Coming to Comics This Summer|date=April 14, 2015 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=April 14, 2015|quote=David Leach, who'll edit the new monthly series, called the comic book 'a true extension of the television series['], promising a glimpse at 'new dimensions of the characters that have captured the audiences worldwide.{{'-}}}}</ref>\n\n=== Games ===\nA mobile game by [[Gameloft]] based on the series, ''The Blacklist: Conspiracy'', was released on June 23, 2016, for Android, iOS and Windows devices.<ref>{{Cite press release|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/gameloft-launches-the-blacklist-conspiracy-for-smartphones-and-tablets-584146551.html|title=Gameloft Launches \"The Blacklist: Conspiracy\" for Smartphones and Tablets|publisher=Gameloft|via=PR Newswire|language=en|access-date=January 20, 2017}}</ref> The game consists of the player as a member of the task force. Players can interact with Reddington and Cooper, other members of the task force, as well as interrogate potential suspects and witnesses. The game mainly consists of searching for missing items in different environments, as well as mini games to further the investigations. Players can also make decisions that alter the route of the story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gameloft.com/en/game/blacklist|title=The Blacklist|website=www.gameloft.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-24}}</ref>\n\n===Spin-off===\n{{main|The Blacklist: Redemption}}\n\nIn March 2016, NBC began developing a spin-off series created by Bokenkamp and Eisendrath, who would also serve as executive producers with Davis and Fox. The project was set to star [[Famke Janssen]] as Susan \"Scottie\" Hargrave (formerly ''Halsted'') and Eggold, in his role as Tom Keen, as well as [[Edi Gathegi]] reprising his role as Matias Solomon. [[Tawny Cypress]] was cast as Nez Rowan, a character already recurring during the third season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/the-blacklist-spinoff-tawny-cypress-cast-1201728743/ |title='The Blacklist' Spinoff: Tawny Cypress Cast |website= Deadline.com}}</ref> Hargrave first appeared on ''The Blacklist'' episode \"Susan Hargrave\", with \"Alexander Kirk\" serving as a [[backdoor pilot]] for the potential series. That episode was written by Bokenkamp and Eisendrath and directed by Michael Dinner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/the-blacklist-spinoff-famke-janssen-star-nbc-1201728137/|title='The Blacklist' Spinoff Starring Famke Janssen In the Works At NBC|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 29, 2016|accessdate=March 29, 2016}}</ref> On May 14, 2016, a pilot for the series, ''The Blacklist: Redemption'', was ordered.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/05/the-blacklist-redemption-spinoff-series-nbc-title-1201755724/|title='The Blacklist' Spinoff Picked Up To Series By NBC, Gets Title|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|website=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref> The series was canceled after one season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/the-blacklist-redemption-canceled-nbc-one-season-1202091823/|title='The Blacklist: Redemption' Canceled By NBC After One Season|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=May 12, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref> Eggold continued his role on ''The Blacklist''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/ryan-eggold-rejoin-the-blacklist-season-5-series-regular-redemption-cancellation-1202091847/|title=Ryan Eggold To Rejoin 'The Blacklist' As Series Regular Following 'Redemption' Cancellation|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=May 12, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote|The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.nbc.com/the-blacklist}}\n* {{IMDb title|2741602|The Blacklist}}\n\n{{sequence\n|prev=''[[New Girl]]''<br />[[Super Bowl XLVIII|2014]]\n|list=[[List of Super Bowl lead-out programs|Super Bowl lead-out program]]<br />''The Blacklist''<br />[[Super Bowl XLIX|2015]]\n|next=''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]''<br />[[Super Bowl 50|2016]]\n}}\n{{The Blacklist}}\n{{NBCNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n{{Portal bar|Television|United States}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Blacklist, The}}\n[[Category:The Blacklist (TV series)| ]]\n[[Category:2013 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:American action television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American crime drama television series]]\n[[Category:Federal Bureau of Investigation in fiction]]\n[[Category:NBC original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by Universal Television]]\n[[Category:Television series by Sony Pictures Television]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Television 